(Blacklist of rude clients/customers in Korean)

271
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:29,830
Attorney Jeon, there are better phrases like "Subject to special management."

272
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:33,170
I'll try using that next time.

273
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:39,660
What's your standard for marking someone as JS?

274
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:41,960
My standard for JS, huh?

275
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:45,000
What does jinsang mean?

276
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,620
Okay. First off, here's number one.

277
00:18:47,620 --> 00:18:50,690
 Loneliness 

278
00:18:50,690 --> 00:18:54,060
People who come because they're lonely when they don't want a divorce.

279
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:56,090
And here's number two.

280
00:18:57,940 --> 00:19:01,730
People who treat us like thieves, saying our fees are too expensive.

281
00:19:01,730 --> 00:19:04,930
And here's number three. Nitpicks.

282
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:06,950
People who keep picking at your words,

283
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:09,030
but don't understand when you actually explain.

284
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:12,640
And lastly, we've got indecision.

285
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:15,210
People who are indecisive are very difficult.

286
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:19,430
Knowing these things will help you a lot later.

287
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:24,310
And also, it's our company policy not to give more than five consultations.

288
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:26,970
You must abide by that rule.

289
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:32,180
I didn't know there was a limitation policy.

290
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:37,400
But aren't the people free to decide how many consultations to receive?

291
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:43,240
This is a law firm, not a therapist's office, where you pay an hourly rate.

292
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:49,520
People get more than five consultations mostly because they can't decide to divorce.

293
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:51,930
It's to clarify that attorneys provide legal representation,

294
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:56,530
but they're the ones who must decide to get a divorce.

295
00:19:57,370 --> 00:20:03,830
Why do newbies get the list of people who come in for their fifth consultation?

296
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:06,170
A neat disposal?

297
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:10,400
It means you should send them back nicely.

298
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,380
Those people are likely to take back

299
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:14,920
their decisions many times, even if we start the litigation.

300
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:18,640
So, it's not appropriate for large law firms to take their cases.

301
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:23,540
I think it's indeed difficult for everyone

302
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:27,190
to decide to get a divorce.

303
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:44,340
But I don't really understand the five-time limit.

304
00:20:44,340 --> 00:20:48,760
Attorney Han, there's no need for you to understand.

305
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:52,120
You just have to obey. Okay?

306
00:20:54,710 --> 00:20:56,880
- Please wrap things up here.
  - Yes. 

307
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,080
Have a good day!

308
00:21:07,650 --> 00:21:09,420
Yes.

309
00:21:12,060 --> 00:21:15,230
Attorney Cha, a fifth consultation client, is here.

310
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:17,470
Attorney Han will be doing the consultation.

311
00:21:17,470 --> 00:21:18,650
Please take her.

312
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:21,110
Yes, I got it.

313
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:29,380
Attorney Cha, do you need anything else?

314
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:35,170
No, I looked because you look pretty today.

315
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:39,730
I see. Thank you.

316
00:21:41,090 --> 00:21:43,170
I guess you've got a date?

317
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:47,670
Yes, I've got plans this evening...

318
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:50,740
with my boyfriend.

319
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:55,290
You had a boyfriend?

320
00:21:55,290 --> 00:21:56,760
I didn't know.

321
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:58,490
You didn't know, huh?

322
00:21:58,490 --> 00:22:01,090
I'll introduce him when I get a chance.

323
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,170
Okay. You can go now.

324
00:22:18,540 --> 00:22:22,290
 You're no longer a wife, a woman, 

325
00:22:22,290 --> 00:22:24,960
 or Jae Hui's mom to me. 

326
00:22:36,430 --> 00:22:40,250
Aren't we talking to Attorney Cha Eun Gyeong?

327
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:43,080
Since you've met Attorney Cha Eun Gyeong four times,

328
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:46,690
it's good to get a second opinion from a different attorney this time.

329
00:22:46,690 --> 00:22:48,850
- Is that so?
 - Of course.

330
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:53,070
Since every attorney has a different opinion, it'll help you more.

331
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,700
How do you do?

332
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,720
Hello, Attorney.

333
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:00,080
Today is my fifth time.

334
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:02,750
So it's the last time, right?

335
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:05,580
Yes, that's true according to our company policy.

336
00:23:05,580 --> 00:23:09,590
I'm paying my money for the consultation, so why won't you let me?

337
00:23:10,470 --> 00:23:13,220
I know, right? Please come inside.

338
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:15,040
A recording?

339
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:17,370
Yes, if you don't record it,

340
00:23:17,370 --> 00:23:21,570
no one will believe your father commits verbal abuse every time he drinks.

341
00:23:21,570 --> 00:23:25,380
You said he's gentle as long as he's sober.

342
00:23:25,380 --> 00:23:27,510
How can I record my own husband?

343
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:29,550
That's a bad thing to do.

344
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:31,540
I came all the way here,

345
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:34,950
but I'm still not sure if getting a divorce is the right thing to do.

346
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:39,380
As long he doesn't drink, for a man his age...

347
00:23:39,380 --> 00:23:42,160
It's true Dad treats me pretty well.

348
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:45,410
The problem is he doesn't want to quit drinking!

349
00:23:45,410 --> 00:23:47,290
Mom, please stop it now.

350
00:23:47,290 --> 00:23:50,660
You even take medication because you can't sleep from the stress.

351
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,120
Why can't you muster up the courage?

352
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:53,760
It's your dad!

353
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,830
You need your dad to walk with you at the wedding!

354
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:57,480
Stop saying it's for my sake!

355
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,340
That's all an excuse.

356
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:01,700
So, will you divorce him after I get married?

357
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:06,470
Now, now. Please calm down.

358
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:11,180
Ma'am, the thing you fear...

359
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:15,530
Is it your husband or the divorce?

360
00:24:15,530 --> 00:24:17,800
My daughter's getting married soon.

361
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:22,520
If her wedding is called off because of my divorce, I can't live.

362
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:25,620
Also, how many years do I have left to live at my age?

363
00:24:25,620 --> 00:24:29,430
Why should I be labeled as a divorcee?

364
00:24:30,410 --> 00:24:33,210
Your daughter already said she's fine.

365
00:24:33,210 --> 00:24:35,690
And, a divorcee, you say?

366
00:24:35,690 --> 00:24:37,760
There's no such thing these days.

367
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:40,060
People will say I abandoned my family

368
00:24:40,060 --> 00:24:42,840
when they don't even know my situation.

369
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:46,810
That's so unfair.

370
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:53,010
So you're saying because of people who don't even know your story,

371
00:24:53,010 --> 00:24:57,270
you're going to endure thirty more years from now, right?

372
00:25:00,580 --> 00:25:04,920
I think he has quite a few assets because our few houses went up in value.

373
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,000
But he won't tell me.

374
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:11,140
When I ask him about it, he just gets furious and yells at me

375
00:25:11,140 --> 00:25:13,900
not to have funny ideas.

376
00:25:16,310 --> 00:25:19,510
You should end your marriage that's just full of fear.

377
00:25:19,510 --> 00:25:23,370
I can live without that man,

378
00:25:23,370 --> 00:25:27,930
but he can't even cook rice without me.

379
00:25:27,930 --> 00:25:32,390
Aigoo! Gosh, he won't starve to death.

380
00:25:32,390 --> 00:25:34,150
He won't starve to death, for sure.

381
00:25:34,150 --> 00:25:38,280
He'll live on cup noodles, get sick, and kick the bucket.

382
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:49,120
If you divide the property, you can take half of what he has.

383
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:53,690
Also, there won't be anyone cursing or looking down on you all day.

384
00:25:53,690 --> 00:25:56,460
So you'll be at peace.

385
00:26:03,310 --> 00:26:07,920
Will it... really be that way?

386
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:11,540
Mom, Dad's not even human.

387
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:14,130
So, please live your life now.

388
00:26:14,130 --> 00:26:17,490
How long will you let Dad walk all over you?

389
00:26:21,810 --> 00:26:25,970
I'll help you take a step forward.

390
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,850
All right.

391
00:26:32,850 --> 00:26:35,350
If you sign here, it's the end.

392
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:38,260
We'll take care of everything from that point on.

393
00:26:38,260 --> 00:26:40,640
Just let me lead you.

394
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:49,700
I told you to wrap up the fifth consultation client, and you bothered to take her case?

395
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:55,870
Yes, Mother couldn't seem to decide, so her daughter and I...

396
00:26:56,480 --> 00:27:00,040
It's Ms. Park Jin Suk, not "Mother."

397
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:04,220
You're not Ms. Park Jin Suk's daughter, are you?

398
00:27:05,310 --> 00:27:09,350
But I'm glad you noticed her daughter will pay for her legal fees.

399
00:27:09,350 --> 00:27:12,930
Knowing where the money will come from is key.

400
00:27:12,930 --> 00:27:16,680
Her daughter was the key to her heart, not the money.

401
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:20,680
Feeling guilty thinking she's abandoning her family even after all that sacrifice...

402
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:24,600
Her child is the only one who will free her from that feeling.

403
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:31,300
I'll make sure to tell the CEO you signed the contract for your first case.

404
00:27:31,300 --> 00:27:33,410
You've earned your keep.

405
00:27:34,210 --> 00:27:36,790
It's true that deciding to divorce is up to you,

406
00:27:36,790 --> 00:27:39,660
but I realized someone has to lead your heart along.

407
00:27:39,660 --> 00:27:42,210
Lead, my foot.

408
00:27:42,990 --> 00:27:45,260
She knew today was the last consultation,

409
00:27:45,260 --> 00:27:48,650
making her sign the contract since she won't have anyone to complain to.

410
00:27:48,650 --> 00:27:51,580
This is why a company's system is important.

411
00:27:51,580 --> 00:27:55,310
Would anyone decide to divorce because of our company system?

412
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:57,520
Yes, Ms. Park Jin Suk.

413
00:27:57,520 --> 00:28:01,400
I say she'll withdraw her compliant during the trial.

414
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:07,700
If I take care of her by her side, she'll be able to stay strong.

415
00:28:07,700 --> 00:28:11,050
She can't go back to that hell again.

416
00:28:11,050 --> 00:28:14,520
So, did you tell her to just trust you again?

417
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,500
I told her to let me lead her.

418
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:23,110
Are you the hero of justice?

419
00:28:23,910 --> 00:28:26,940
Attorney Han, let's be honest here.

420
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:30,730
You just wanted to teach him a lesson.

421
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:33,100
He needs to be taught a lesson.

422
00:28:33,100 --> 00:28:37,940
Rather than that, it's more important to know whether she can really live alone.

423
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:40,490
Divorce isn't for everyone.

424
00:28:42,550 --> 00:28:45,010
Are you saying there's a qualification for divorce?

425
00:28:45,010 --> 00:28:47,600
Of course, there is.

426
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:50,760
Someone like Ms. Park Jin Suk could never

427
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:55,820
live alone because she's too fragile, even if she gets a fortune in the division of property.

428
00:28:57,330 --> 00:28:59,820
What about you, Attorney Cha?

429
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:03,780
You meet the qualifications for divorce.

430
00:29:05,490 --> 00:29:07,440
So suddenly?

431
00:29:08,250 --> 00:29:11,720
Is it also because of the social pressure for you?

432
00:29:20,190 --> 00:29:23,080
Put the trash in the trash can.

433
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:27,940
You need to live every day of your precious life to its fullest.

434
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:33,450
Even if you throw trash away, food waste goes into the food waste bin.

435
00:29:33,450 --> 00:29:38,760
Reusable items go in the recycle bin after a good wash.

436
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:41,250
It's not all that simple.

437
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:43,910
You've done recycling before, right?

438
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,950
Yes, I live alone.

439
00:29:47,950 --> 00:29:50,750
Is that so? I see.

440
00:29:56,820 --> 00:29:58,600
- Attorneys!
 - Hey.

441
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,910
Did you eat?

442
00:29:59,910 --> 00:30:01,920
We did.

443
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:04,680
What did you have?

444
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,800
Are you going to the court today?

445
00:30:14,310 --> 00:30:18,410
 Yu Ri, someone I know from church said they can introduce you to a good man. 

446
00:30:18,410 --> 00:30:19,730
 I'll set up the date. Okay? 

447
00:30:19,730 --> 00:30:22,730
 Since you got a job, you need to start seeing a man. 

448
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:24,900
Gosh, seriously.

449
00:30:24,900 --> 00:30:26,140
Did you have a good lunch?

450
00:30:26,140 --> 00:30:28,240
- Yes.
 - You're back.

451
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:30,370
Attorney Han, did you have coffee?

452
00:30:30,370 --> 00:30:32,380
Yes, I did.

453
00:30:32,380 --> 00:30:33,990
- Let's have one more. 
- What?

454
00:30:33,990 --> 00:30:35,270
- Outside.
 - W-Why?

455
00:30:35,270 --> 00:30:37,450
To get some exercise, too.

456
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:41,430
So, you took the case? What did Attorney Cha say?

457
00:30:41,430 --> 00:30:43,830
She said, "Why bother?"

458
00:30:43,830 --> 00:30:45,560
How annoying.

459
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:49,230
Attorney Han, can I ask you one question, purely out of curiosity?

460
00:30:49,230 --> 00:30:52,270
Why don't you ever do what the company tells you?

461
00:30:52,270 --> 00:30:54,000
- Me?
 - Yes.

462
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:58,120
Do you have a rebellious spirit you couldn't resolve when you were young?

463
00:30:58,120 --> 00:31:00,690
No! I don't have anything like that.

464
00:31:00,690 --> 00:31:06,060
I'm just following my attorney's conscience every moment.

465
00:31:06,060 --> 00:31:09,220
Conscience, huh? Respect.

466
00:31:09,220 --> 00:31:11,690
You live a really tiresome life.

467
00:31:11,690 --> 00:31:14,670
Cha Eun Gyeong is the one who lives a tiresome life.

468
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:17,930
Can't she just give a compliment for once?

469
00:31:17,930 --> 00:31:22,120
Gosh, how's she any different from Park Jin Suk?

470
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:24,570
Why? Attorney Cha said she won't get a divorce?

471
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:26,050
She said she won't!

472
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:28,820
Does it make sense for a divorce attorney to live with a man

473
00:31:28,820 --> 00:31:32,070
who cheated on her out of fear of the social stigma?

474
00:31:32,070 --> 00:31:34,210
Isn't she embarrassed?

475
00:31:34,210 --> 00:31:40,100
Attorney Cha isn't the type to be afraid of the social stigma of getting a divorce.

476
00:31:40,100 --> 00:31:43,700
Well, couldn't it be because of her child?

477
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:50,690
You also knew that I was talking about Attorney Cha?

478
00:31:50,690 --> 00:31:52,590
Me? I had no idea.

479
00:31:52,590 --> 00:31:57,630
I just cast a leading question, and you took the bait, Han Yu Ri.

480
00:31:57,630 --> 00:32:00,530
Wow, so that happened to Attorney Cha, huh?

481
00:32:00,530 --> 00:32:02,410
If I had a wife like Attorney Cha,

482
00:32:02,410 --> 00:32:04,300
I'd make her my queen and serve her.

483
00:32:04,300 --> 00:32:08,330
Attorney Jeon, you'll keep the secret, right?

484
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:10,560
Excuse me. I'm also an attorney, okay?

485
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:13,030
Isn't confidentiality a legal duty?

486
00:32:13,030 --> 00:32:16,330
- You mean it, right? 
- Of course!

487
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:23,330
I guess you sleep fine even with two cups of coffee.

488
00:32:23,330 --> 00:32:25,040
I pass out the moment my head—

489
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:28,050
Wait, how did you know this is my second cup of coffee?

490
00:32:28,050 --> 00:32:30,860
- Leading question. 
- Aigoo.

491
00:32:30,860 --> 00:32:34,190
I just had a quick blind date during lunch.

492
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:36,350
I got caught. How embarrassing.

493
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:37,900
Why didn't you meet in the evening?

494
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:39,870
I have to get off work on time

495
00:32:39,870 --> 00:32:42,690
and have chimaek* with you in the evening.
(Fried chicken and beer.)

496
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:46,130
Attorney Jeon, do you really like me?

497
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:47,750
I really like you.

498
00:32:47,750 --> 00:32:49,770
Love your colleague, love your country. Right?

499
00:32:49,770 --> 00:32:52,120
Let's be friends for a long time.

500
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:54,370
Stop being so clingy.

501
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:57,950
Why? Let's work together forever. Don't quit, okay?

502
00:33:12,020 --> 00:33:13,790
N-No.

503
00:33:13,790 --> 00:33:17,540
It's okay. You don't need to put them on.

504
00:33:20,940 --> 00:33:22,860
Attorney Han,

505
00:33:22,860 --> 00:33:28,820
I'm the only one who will wipe his butt when he gets old and sick.

506
00:33:28,820 --> 00:33:33,090
So, I'm not sure if I can abandon him like this.

507
00:33:35,690 --> 00:33:39,060
Did you marry him to wipe his butt when he gets old?

