00:35:13,110 --> 00:35:14,990
Who's this?

534
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,770
Yes? Hello?

535
00:35:19,770 --> 00:35:26,080
 Hey, are you happy to live like that, lying to people? 

536
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:28,680
- What did you say?
 -  What was that thing called? 

537
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:33,860
You wrote a complete fiction in the thing called a complaint!

538
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:36,880
Excuse me, it's not fiction.

539
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:40,130
That's the sorrow in Park Jin Suk's heart.

540
00:35:40,130 --> 00:35:42,490
Did you see me cursing at my wife?

541
00:35:42,490 --> 00:35:43,680
Do you have proof?

542
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:48,840
 And all my friends beat up their wives once in a while! 

543
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:51,330
 But they aren't even sorry. 

544
00:35:51,330 --> 00:35:54,910
- I even say I'm sorry, and I buy her presents—
 -  Aigoo. 

545
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:57,200
Do you want an award or something?

546
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:59,640
I'll sue you for false accusations!

547
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:04,890
 How dare a woman run away from home without preparing her husband's dinner? 

548
00:36:04,890 --> 00:36:08,270
No one in this world will prepare dinner for someone like you.

549
00:36:08,270 --> 00:36:09,610
You should've done better!

550
00:36:09,610 --> 00:36:12,840
Tell Park Jin Suk to come home right now. I won't let her be!

551
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:16,440
 Ms. Park Jin Suk will never go home again. 

552
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,960
I'll make that happen.

553
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:22,490
 Hey! If you don't quit this right now, I'll kill myself! 

554
00:36:22,490 --> 00:36:24,360
You said you'll kill who?

555
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:28,850
I said I'll kill myself!

556
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,550
Attorney Jeong!

557
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:39,150
Aren't you going home, Attorney Han?

558
00:36:39,950 --> 00:36:42,370
I still have a lot of work to do.

559
00:36:42,370 --> 00:36:44,940
I heard you took a new case.

560
00:36:44,940 --> 00:36:47,990
Good job. It's not an easy thing to do.

561
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:54,510
Attorney Cha said I shouldn't have taken the case.

562
00:36:54,510 --> 00:36:57,230
- Thank you.
 - Gosh...

563
00:36:57,230 --> 00:37:03,560
Why are people unable to decide to divorce in such ridiculous situations?

564
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:05,420
Do they lack courage that much?

565
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:09,100
They're probably afraid, not that they lack courage.

566
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:14,110
Because even the strongest person fears being alone.

567
00:37:18,970 --> 00:37:21,460
Man, you're quite dependable.

568
00:37:21,460 --> 00:37:23,040
Fighting.

569
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,610
Yes, fighting.

570
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:28,630
- Hang in there.
 - Yes, please take care.

571
00:37:33,470 --> 00:37:35,940
Yes. Thank you.

572
00:37:49,910 --> 00:37:53,150
Oh, yes. About that, yesterday...

573
00:37:53,150 --> 00:37:56,580
Yes, yes. Yes, please wrap it up that way.

574
00:37:56,580 --> 00:37:58,380
Okay.

575
00:38:23,850 --> 00:38:25,800
- Thank you.
 - Thank you.

576
00:38:28,520 --> 00:38:30,440
- Yes.
 -  Seonbae, are you done with the radio? 

577
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,840
 Yes. Why? 

578
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:35,810
Please buy me a drink.

579
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:40,370
Jeong Wu Jin asked me to buy him a drink, huh?

580
00:38:43,350 --> 00:38:47,020
You used to buy me a drink here after giving me a good scolding before. Right?

581
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:49,400
Did you even listen when I scolded you?

582
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:54,430
You used to say yes, yes,  but did not actually listen in the end.

583
00:38:54,430 --> 00:38:56,460
You remember it completly opposite.

584
00:38:56,460 --> 00:38:58,270
I pretended not to listen,

585
00:38:58,270 --> 00:39:01,700
but I engraved everything you said in my heart.

586
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:04,450
I was just trying to put my tiny pride forward back then.

587
00:39:04,450 --> 00:39:07,310
You're the one giving me an earful every day now,

588
00:39:07,310 --> 00:39:09,180
saying I've got a bad temper.

589
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:12,810
I'm just telling you to be gentle to the kids.

590
00:39:12,810 --> 00:39:16,850
If they quit again, you're the one who will be scolded by the CEO.

591
00:39:16,850 --> 00:39:20,980
Am I someone who's afraid of others' opinions?

592
00:39:21,940 --> 00:39:24,610
Yes, you're afraid.

593
00:39:29,130 --> 00:39:33,190
Hey, you know Han Yu Ri accepted her first case, right?

594
00:39:34,090 --> 00:39:36,100
Yeah, I know.

595
00:39:36,100 --> 00:39:38,580
It looked like she was going to quit soon.

596
00:39:39,180 --> 00:39:43,600
If I think about it, she's just like you-know-who when she was new.

597
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:45,690
Me?

598
00:39:45,690 --> 00:39:47,460
Me?

599
00:39:47,460 --> 00:39:51,200
What are you saying? We're totally different.

600
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:58,620
By the way, why did the Director suddenly quit being our advisor?

601
00:39:58,620 --> 00:40:01,690
Are things not good between you two?

602
00:40:04,100 --> 00:40:07,210
What are you saying? He's just busy.

603
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:17,200
Seonbae, you don't express your feelings at work or home, right?

604
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,720
What's the use in doing that?

605
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:22,870
We'd only burden each other.

606
00:40:22,870 --> 00:40:26,310
You should do it somewhere, at the very least.

607
00:40:26,310 --> 00:40:28,780
It's lonely to live like that.

608
00:40:33,290 --> 00:40:35,980
Attorney Jeong, you've never been married.

609
00:40:37,290 --> 00:40:43,330
You could say a married couple's relationship has more at stake

610
00:40:43,330 --> 00:40:45,830
than coworkers' and friends'.

611
00:40:45,830 --> 00:40:49,690
So, there's also a need to exist functionally rather than emotionally,

612
00:40:49,690 --> 00:40:52,060
because it's a long-term relationship.

613
00:40:54,990 --> 00:40:58,280
But you'll have a hard time as a result.

614
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,720
Why would I have a hard time?

615
00:41:05,720 --> 00:41:08,410
Where did that come from suddenly?

616
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:13,560
Seonbae.

617
00:41:14,260 --> 00:41:17,460
You know I want to help you, right?

618
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:21,030
What's gotten into you?

619
00:41:21,030 --> 00:41:23,300
Mind your own business.

620
00:42:20,340 --> 00:42:22,100
What's this?

621
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:26,620
Could it be she lives here?

622
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:30,500
 One Space 

623
00:42:35,250 --> 00:42:38,020
She really lives in the same place.

624
00:42:38,020 --> 00:42:40,200
Geez!

625
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:43,890
- Yu Ri- My goodness!
 - O-Oh, my!

626
00:42:43,890 --> 00:42:45,790
- M-Mom!
 - Why?

627
00:42:45,790 --> 00:42:47,800
Y-You didn't even call.

628
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:49,970
I brought some greens side dishes.

629
00:42:49,970 --> 00:42:53,570
Gosh! I rarely eat at home.

630
00:42:53,570 --> 00:42:56,100
You'll eat if there are side dishes.

631
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:58,280
That's how your Dad always was.

632
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,900
He said to make sure you're fed well

633
00:43:00,900 --> 00:43:04,280
because that's the most important job for me.

634
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:07,680
Mom, that's gaslighting.

635
00:43:07,680 --> 00:43:11,390
Why is your most important job feeding me?

636
00:43:11,390 --> 00:43:13,290
Try to think critically now.

637
00:43:13,290 --> 00:43:16,990
Think critically, my foot. He was right.

638
00:43:18,490 --> 00:43:23,660
Don't you hate him for backstabbing you while saying those things?

639
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:27,770
I thought he only worked his butt off to feed his family,

640
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:32,460
but I'm glad now since he got to stab me in the back before he died.

641
00:43:34,340 --> 00:43:37,350
Something happens to your brain when you get married, right?

642
00:43:37,350 --> 00:43:39,900
What's wrong with my brain?

643
00:43:39,900 --> 00:43:41,760
Just go.

644
00:43:44,850 --> 00:43:46,210
Ma'am, we meet again.

645
00:43:46,210 --> 00:43:48,390
Seriously. We meet again.

646
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:50,490
Attorney Han.

647
00:43:51,870 --> 00:43:53,530
We met once last time.

648
00:43:53,530 --> 00:43:58,290
I found out she works at your office while we were chatting last time.

649
00:43:58,290 --> 00:43:59,760
What an interesting connection.

650
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,690
I know, right?

651
00:44:01,690 --> 00:44:05,220
- Connection, my foot.
 - Your boyfriend isn't here today.

652
00:44:05,220 --> 00:44:07,230
He was so tall and handsome.

653
00:44:07,230 --> 00:44:10,420
Both of you seem so kind that you don't need law.

654
00:44:10,420 --> 00:44:12,160
 They live recklessly even with the law. 

655
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:15,010
I think he'll be working late tonight.

656
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:19,790
I'll make beef brisket soybean paste stew using the recipe you told me last time.

657
00:44:19,790 --> 00:44:21,820
- Yes.
 - The snail soybean paste stew was delicious.

658
00:44:21,820 --> 00:44:24,360
Gosh, I'm glad.

659
00:44:25,530 --> 00:44:27,950
Aigoo, go ahead.

660
00:44:32,690 --> 00:44:35,810
Stop looking at your phone and come eat.

661
00:44:42,700 --> 00:44:44,930
- Mom.
 - Yeah?

662
00:44:44,930 --> 00:44:49,430
Please don't go around making friends with just anybody.

663
00:44:49,430 --> 00:44:51,190
What do you mean, anybody?

664
00:44:51,190 --> 00:44:54,500
She's your coworker and neighbor.

665
00:44:55,760 --> 00:45:00,850
Did you forget our neighbor was actually Dad's mistress?

666
00:45:00,850 --> 00:45:05,140
Aigoo, the soup cooked so nicely.

667
00:45:06,670 --> 00:45:08,570
No way.

668
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:12,810
You're not pitying Dad, are you?

669
00:45:12,810 --> 00:45:15,370
You're the pitiful one, not Dad.

670
00:45:15,370 --> 00:45:16,910
You're the victim.

671
00:45:16,910 --> 00:45:18,460
Victim and offender...

672
00:45:18,460 --> 00:45:21,390
Is everything a courtroom in your eyes?

673
00:45:21,390 --> 00:45:24,400
Even outside of court, a victim is a victim, and an offender is an offender.

674
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:26,690
So delicious.

675
00:45:31,990 --> 00:45:34,730
By the way,

676
00:45:34,730 --> 00:45:40,270
why did you try not to divorce Dad when he cheated on you?

677
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:45,340
Just because.

678
00:45:46,350 --> 00:45:48,210
Because of me?

679
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:53,640
I was hesitant that your studies would suffer because of me.

680
00:45:54,430 --> 00:45:57,300
I also tried to understand your dad.

681
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:01,170
- Wait, Mom. Look at it this way, then. 
- Try this.

682
00:46:01,870 --> 00:46:04,240
The causality is wrong here.

683
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:08,060
You're saying I'd suffer because of your decision to divorce,

684
00:46:08,060 --> 00:46:12,360
not because of Dad, who cheated on you?

685
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,640
How can you think that way?

686
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:19,060
Mom, it's so frustrating for me! Seriously.

687
00:46:19,060 --> 00:46:22,510
Why can't people just get a divorce for crying out loud?

688
00:46:22,510 --> 00:46:24,030
I'm more frustrated by you.

689
00:46:24,030 --> 00:46:26,600
Try having your own kid later.

690
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:31,060
Did you study that hard to become an ambassador for divorce?

691
00:46:31,980 --> 00:46:37,930
Are you saying divorce is bad and that it's a social evil with no end?

692
00:46:38,870 --> 00:46:42,890
Sure! You can keep living in Joseon by yourself, then.

693
00:46:42,890 --> 00:46:44,650
I can't live in Joseon.

694
00:46:44,650 --> 00:46:47,940
I'm a divorcee. A modern divorcee.

695
00:46:49,200 --> 00:46:52,850
Well, why do you keep ignoring my texts, Ms. Modern?

696
00:46:53,790 --> 00:46:55,480
Because I've got my reasons.

697
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:57,240
I'm going to set it up, okay?

698
00:46:57,240 --> 00:46:59,660
I'll change the passcode for the lock, okay?

699
00:46:59,660 --> 00:47:02,580
You got a job now, so you should hurry.

700
00:47:02,580 --> 00:47:05,790
All right! Fine! Fine!

701
00:47:05,790 --> 00:47:08,760
"Fine"? You said that yourself, okay?

702
00:47:09,700 --> 00:47:11,090
 Client Park Jin Suk  
 Have some rolled omelet, too.

703
00:47:11,090 --> 00:47:13,620
M-Mom, hold on.

704
00:47:15,730 --> 00:47:18,960
Yes, Ms. Park Jin Suk. Did something happen?

705
00:47:18,960 --> 00:47:21,200
Hi, Attorney Han.

706
00:47:21,200 --> 00:47:26,210
Is it okay for me to continue doing this?

707
00:47:26,210 --> 00:47:28,000
- What?
 -  I mean... 

708
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:33,240
 he's begging me to drop the case, saying he'll never drink again. 

