00:47:35,740 --> 00:47:38,670
N-No, no, no, it's a bit different this time.

711
00:47:38,670 --> 00:47:41,400
He always cursed when he got drunk and begged when he got sober.

712
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:45,880
But he's begging while he's drunk this time.

713
00:47:45,880 --> 00:47:50,640
-  What's he saying this time? 
- Y-Yes?

714
00:47:50,640 --> 00:47:52,580
He wants me to come make him food.

715
00:47:52,580 --> 00:47:54,970
 He said he'll really quit drinking. 

716
00:47:54,970 --> 00:47:59,850
So I wonder if I should go make him some soup, at least.

717
00:48:00,730 --> 00:48:06,250
So, you're going to go back to cook food again?

718
00:48:06,250 --> 00:48:08,590
Don't believe a word.

719
00:48:08,590 --> 00:48:12,950
He's never eaten food other than what I made him.

720
00:48:13,410 --> 00:48:16,310
 Gosh, I'm sick of this. 

721
00:48:17,010 --> 00:48:19,350
Don't decide anything for now.

722
00:48:19,350 --> 00:48:21,410
I'll see you tomorrow.

723
00:48:24,530 --> 00:48:28,470
Why are you doing this to me?

724
00:48:29,520 --> 00:48:31,950
Hurry up and eat.

725
00:48:48,710 --> 00:48:50,790
Park Jin Suk!

726
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:55,400
 Emergency Center  
 I told you he might kill himself!

727
00:48:55,400 --> 00:48:56,720
Mom!

728
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:59,210
It's not the attorney's fault.

729
00:48:59,210 --> 00:49:02,200
Did she force you to file the complaint?

730
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:04,250
I'm so sick of this.

731
00:49:04,930 --> 00:49:09,200
An unlucky wench like me can't even get a divorce.

732
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:10,600
I knew this would happen.

733
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:13,540
That's why I said I'm not going to do it!

734
00:49:13,540 --> 00:49:15,950
What kind of nonsense is this?

735
00:49:15,950 --> 00:49:18,060
The attorney was trying to help us.

736
00:49:18,060 --> 00:49:19,910
Shut it!

737
00:49:20,470 --> 00:49:22,030
I don't want to see you.

738
00:49:22,030 --> 00:49:25,910
Leave. Go away. Aigoo, get out of here!

739
00:49:26,610 --> 00:49:30,730
Let go! Aigoo, I'm sick of this.

740
00:49:46,240 --> 00:49:48,500
I'm sick of this.

741
00:50:01,060 --> 00:50:03,700
How was the hospital visit?

742
00:50:07,490 --> 00:50:11,830
What should I do with the case now?

743
00:50:11,830 --> 00:50:13,900
Just leave it for now.

744
00:50:13,900 --> 00:50:16,910
If he dies, Estate Law will take it over and process it.

745
00:50:16,910 --> 00:50:21,900
If he doesn't die, you can withdraw it according to what she says.

746
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:26,360
Did something like this happen to you, too?

747
00:50:26,360 --> 00:50:27,470
Of course.

748
00:50:27,470 --> 00:50:32,400
As an attorney, you'll see a lot of people who kill themselves after receiving a complaint.

749
00:50:34,460 --> 00:50:37,480
But it's not the attorney's fault.

750
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:40,810
Do you think so?

751
00:50:41,430 --> 00:50:45,200
Is it the prosecutor's fault if you kill yourself after receiving an indictment?

752
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:49,030
Is it the tax official's fault if you die after receiving a tax collection notice?

753
00:50:49,030 --> 00:50:51,020
It's not, is it?

754
00:50:57,340 --> 00:51:00,700
Convincing a hesitant client to decide to divorce

755
00:51:00,700 --> 00:51:05,440
with your shallow sense of duty and pathetic sense of justice?

756
00:51:07,580 --> 00:51:10,330
You shouldn't have done that.

757
00:51:11,450 --> 00:51:14,720
Do you also think I instigated her to get a divorce?

758
00:51:14,720 --> 00:51:17,160
I didn't say you instigated her.

759
00:51:20,120 --> 00:51:23,460
Then, what should I have done instead?

760
00:51:25,560 --> 00:51:28,830
Please tell my mom to get a divorce.

761
00:51:28,830 --> 00:51:31,660
I never say such things.

762
00:51:32,280 --> 00:51:37,190
A divorce attorney doesn't decide if you should divorce or not.

